
[1]pacific

   PACIFIC, a. [L., to make peace. See Peace.]

   1. Peace-making; conciliatory; suited to make or restore peace; adapted
   to reconcile differences; mild; appeasing; as, to offer pacific
   propositions to a belligerent power. The measures proposed are in their
   nature pacific.

   2. Calm; tranquil; as a pacific state of things.

   PACIFIC, n. The appellation given to the ocean situated between America
      on the west, and Asia; so called on account of its exemption from
                              violent tempests.
